    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 25,
        "summary": "David pleads for truth and asks for pardon\u2014Mercy and truth are for those who keep the commandments.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Unto thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 86:4; 143:8.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O my God, I trust in thee: let me not be ashamed, let not mine enemies triumph over me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith; Trust in God.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, let none that wait on thee be ashamed: let them be ashamed which transgress without cause.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worthiness.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Shew me thy ways, O Lord; teach me thy paths.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 33:13 (12\u201313); Ps. 143:8 (5\u201312); John 14:6; D&C 50:17 (17\u201320); 76:2 (1\u20135); 79:2.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lead me in thy truth, and teach me: for thou art the God of my salvation; on thee do I wait all the day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guidance, Divine; Leadership.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 49:18; Prov. 20:22; Isa. 40:31; 2\u00a0Ne. 6:13 (7, 13).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Remember, O Lord, thy tender mercies and thy lovingkindnesses; for they have been ever of old.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Mercy of.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Remember not the sins of my youth, nor my transgressions: according to thy mercy remember thou me for thy goodness' sake, O Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 13:26; D&C 20:5; 58:42; JS\u2014H 1:28 (28\u201329).",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 51:1.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Good and upright is the Lord: therefore will he teach sinners in the way.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Education.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The meek will he guide in judgment: and the meek will he teach his way.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guidance, Divine.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "All the paths of the Lord are mercy and truth unto such as keep his covenant and his testimonies.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For thy name's sake, O Lord, pardon mine iniquity; for it is great.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 109:21.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "What man is he that feareth the Lord? him shall he teach in the way that he shall choose.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "His soul shall dwell at ease; and his seed shall inherit the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Destiny of.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The secret of the Lord is with them that fear him; and he will shew them his covenant.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mysteries of Godliness.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Mine eyes are ever toward the Lord; for he shall pluck my feet out of the net.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 141:8; D&C 4:5.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 9:15; 31:4.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Turn thee unto me, and have mercy upon me; for I am desolate and afflicted.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Mercy of.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The troubles of my heart are enlarged: O bring thou me out of my distresses.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Look upon mine affliction and my pain; and forgive all my sins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pain.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Consider mine enemies; for they are many; and they hate me with cruel hatred.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cruelty.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O keep my soul, and deliver me: let me not be ashamed; for I put my trust in thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust in God.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 729
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let integrity and uprightness preserve me; for I wait on thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Redeem Israel, O God, out of all his troubles.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 21:8; Ps. 130:8; D&C 84:99 (99\u2013100).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}